If you purchase goods or services directly from us

If you purchase a licence to use in-game virtual currency or virtual items in a game you play on <domain>, our third-party payment processor will collect the billing and financial information it needs to process your charges. Note that this third party payment processor will be the controller in relation to certain processing relating to the transaction. You will be informed of their identity and provided with information on how they process your personal data at the time the payment is made.

This may include any of the above information plus:
- Sales information, including transaction history and payment information
- Bank account information
- Credit card information
They will process this information in order to:
- Process your payment or refund your payment
- Identify you
- Protect you and us from fraud
- Prevent crime

<App>  may obtain the billing and payment information that you provide when your purchase is processed by someone else (like Apple or Google) such as when you purchase something in a game you play on a social network or that you downloaded on your mobile device. Our Terms of Service explain our policies and terms relevant to our charges, billing practices, third-party credits and virtual currencies. Please note that purchases of third party credits or currencies may also be subject to those parties’ policies.

4、Lawful basis of processing

We process all of the above data in the pursuit of our legitimate business interests, including the pursuit of new business, new customers and revenue streams, as well as the development of new, improved apps and games and building our share of the market, our reputation and brands.
In some cases we also need to process the personal data pursuant to a contract with you or a third party, such as Apple or Google, or to comply with a legal obligation.
Where we have not indicated that a lawful basis other than legitimate interest applies, you are entitled to object to the processing of the persona data.

5、Rights of EU Residents

Residents of the European Economic Area (EEA) have additional rights, including the right to obtain copies of personal data and to file complaints with local data protection authorities. Data may be transferred outside the EEA to jurisdictions with varying levels of protection, and by using the App, you explicitly agree to such transfers. Consent may be revoked at any time.

6、Third-Party Service Providers
We will share your information with third-party companies to perform services on our behalf, like processing payments, analyzing data, optimizing game play, e-mail delivery, hosting services, customer service and to help us in our marketing efforts, including managing and delivering contextual and tailored advertisements. We contractually require these third-party service providers to maintain the confidentiality of the information we share with them, and we contractually require them not use your information for anything other than to provide services on our behalf.

7、Cookies, analytics and automated information collection
We and service providers acting on our behalf, like Aliyun SLS, store log files and use tracking technologies such as:
- cookies, which are small pieces of data transferred to your mobile device or computer for record-keeping purposes;
- web beacons, which let us know if a certain page was visited or whether an e-mail was opened;
- tracking pixels, which allow us or our advertising partners to advertise more efficiently and effectively; and
- local shared objects, also known as flash cookies, which help us to reduce fraud, remember your in-game preferences and speed up load times.
- We and our service providers use these log files, tags, and tracking technologies to collect and analyze certain kinds of technical information, including:
- IP addresses;
- the type of computer or mobile device you are using;
- your operating system version;
- your mobile device’s identifiers, like your MAC Address, Identifier For Advertising (IDFA), and/or International Mobile Equipment Identity (IMEI);
- your device types;
- your device language;
- referring and exit pages, and URLs;
- platform type;
- the number of clicks on a page or feature;
- domain names;
- landing pages;
- pages viewed and the order of those pages;
- the amount of time spent on particular pages; and
- game state and the date and time of activity on our websites or games.
- In some cases, we will connect this information with your social network ID or <App>  player ID.
Please note that companies delivering advertisements on our Services may also use cookies or other technologies as described below, and those practices are subject to those companies’ own policies.  More information on how third parties may use your data in our Services go to Appendix A and Appendix B further below.
8、Personal data concerning you that we may process on behalf of others
For a personalized advertisement experience, the advertising networks and their partners, some of which are listed below may collect or receive device information from our apps and other apps that include personal and non-personal information, such as advertising (or ad) identifiers, IP address, or other information regarding the delivery of advertisements and your interaction with them, inventory of installed apps and/or other tracking technologies to provide measurement services, personalization, ad selection, delivery, reporting, and optimize targeted ads. You can learn more about how each handles your data by accessing their respective privacy notices using the hyperlinks below.

9、How We Share Your Information
We may disclose or publish aggregated information (information about you and other players collectively that is not intended to specifically identify you) and other non-personal information about our players for industry analysis, demographic profiling, marketing, analytics, advertising, and other business purposes.
In addition, we may share your information (which may include personal information) with third parties (in other words, parties other than <App>) or allow third parties to collect this information from our Services

10、Privacy policies of linked third-party services and advertisers
Our websites and games may contain advertisements from Third-Party Services, which are companies other than <App> that may link to their own websites, online services or mobile applications. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or the content of these Third-Party Services. If you have any questions about how these Third-Party Services use your information, you should review their policies and contact them directly.

11、Protection of Children's Information
We do not intentionally collect information from children under the age of 13 (or under 16 in the EEA). If a parent or guardian believes their child has provided us with personal information without their consent, they should contact us immediately, and we will take steps to remove such information.

12、Retention of Information
We retain your information only for the period necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, to comply with legal obligations, or until you request its deletion. As such, we will store your information for the duration of your interaction with the mobile application provided as part of our Services. After that period, information will be permanently deleted or de-identified for use in analytics.

13、Security of your information
We implement security measures to help protect the security of your information both online and offline. We take steps to ensure that your data is treated securely and in accordance with this Privacy Policy. 

We use industry-standard security measures, including physical, administrative, and technical safeguards, as well as encryption where necessary, to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction.

While we take precautions against possible security breaches of our Services and our customer databases and records, no website or Internet transmission is completely secure. We cannot guarantee that unauthorized access, hacking, data loss, or other breaches will never occur, and we cannot guarantee the security of your information while it is being transmitted to our Service. Any transmission is at your own risk. If you have questions about the security of our websites, please contact us at <Email>.

14、 Changes to our privacy policy
We may need to update this Privacy Notice to reflect changes to our data processing practices. If we do this and the changes are material, we will post a notice on  <Email> for at least 8 days before the changes are made.  You can see the date this Privacy Notice was last revised at the top of the page.

15、Your rights
The applicable data protection laws give you certain specific rights in relation to the processing of personal data that concerns you.
Please note that not all these apply in all circumstances.  However, you are always welcome to contact us with any request relating to processing of your personal data. Even where we are not obliged by law to comply with your request, we will try to accommodate your wishes.
- Access – you have the right to access personal data concerning you and certain information about how and why we are processing it;
- Rectification – you have the right to have any inaccurate or incomplete personal data rectified without undue delay;
- Erasure – Sometimes called the ‘right to be forgotten’, in certain circumstances, you have the right to have personal data that concerns you erased without undue delay;
- Restriction – in certain circumstances, you have the right to have our processing of personal data concerning you restricted;
- Data portability – in certain limited circumstances, you have the right to receive any personal data concerning you that you have provided to us, in a structured, commonly-used and machine-readable format, and the right to transmit those data to another controller without hindrance; and
- Objection – in certain circumstances, you have the right to object to the processing of personal data carried out by us or on our behalf where it concerns you.

16、Contact Us
If you have any questions about your personal data or this Privacy Policy, please contact us at <Email>.

